===Noun===
'''language''' (''[[uncountable]] and [[countable]]; plural:'' '''languages''')

#<!--DefA-->(''uncountable'') The expression of an understanding &mdash; see [http://www.ourcivilisation.com/undrstnd.htm "Language is Understanding"]
#<!--DefB-->A system of [[communication]] using the spoken word or using symbols that represent words or sounds.
#:''the English '''language'''''
#<!--DefC-->(''uncountable'') The ability to communicate using words.
#:''the gift of '''language'''''
#<!--DefD-->(''uncountable'') A nonverbal system of communication.
#:''sign '''language'''''
#<!--DefE-->(''computing'') A [[computer language]].
#<!--DefF-->(''uncountable'') The [[vocabulary]] used in a particular [[specialist]] field.
#:''legal '''language'''''
#<!--DefG-->(''uncountable'') The particular words used in speech or a passage of text.
#:''The '''language''' he used to talk to me was obscene.''
#:''The '''language''' used in the law does not permit any other interpretation.''

